        <p> ___Twig_token_1___ The Elbe literally fell into the water. We decided to ignore the alarm clock, fell asleep and have breakfast in peace, while the rain drummed evenly onto the roof. </p>
        <p> After the cozy start of the day we checked out and parked our motorhome in the parking lot in front of the campsite. Thanks to the guest card, we were able to take the bus into downtown Pirna free of charge - an offer that we were happy to use. </p>
        <p> The old town of Pirna surprised us with its charm. The small streets, historical facades and nicely decorated shop windows invited to stroll and we discovered sayings on various shop windows. We found the saying particularly nice in the windows of a bakery caf&eacute;-on a window: "I'm so full, I don't like Bla ...", followed by the next window with "Oh, cake." Small details that are remembered. </p>
        <p> At the market square we discovered a restaurant with a pleasant atmosphere and good music. Although the menu appealed to us directly, we were still too full of breakfast, so we decided to come back later. Instead, we continued to drive and finally ended up in a fabric shop. Actually, we just wanted to look in - in the end we left it with three meters of fabric in two colors. The planned sofa cushions at home can finally go into implementation. </p>

