        <p> The bookshop nearby was also taken with us - a new book also hiked into our pocket. Then we returned to the restaurant from the morning. The decision to eat there turned out to be the right one - the food was excellent, the ambience was right, and we stayed for a while. </p>
        <p> In the afternoon we continued to L&uuml;bbenau. A short detour initially led us to a repo market, but without greater find. Our planned parking space for the night was directly opposite - in front of a hotel with a swimming pool. </p>
        <p> Since we had no desire for the motorhome that day, we decided to visit the hotel bar without further ado. With a drink, a pleasant atmosphere and the new book, we let the day fade away. </p>
        <p> Back in the camper we prepared a late dinner, watched a film and ended the day relaxed. </p>
